        "paragraph_index": 5,
        "text": "What’s interesting:\n- The trivalent lanthanides are extensively studied, with mid–heavy Ln(III) like Gd and Dy showing hundreds of ligands and measurements. That mirrors the practical importance of their coordination chemistry.\n- Sc(III) and Y(III) are present but with leaner coverage than the lanthanides.\n- Non‑trivalent states pop up as curiosities: Ce(IV) has a handful of entries, Eu(II) has very few, and Yb(II) is essentially absent in this dataset — consistent with the stability of Ln(III) under typical aqueous conditions.",
